          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "124Sn target of thickness 2.47 +/- 0.04 mg/cm2, which",
                " was measured using the Rutherford backscattering",
                " method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Compton suppressed clover detectors were",
                " placed outside the scattering chamber in the",
                " horizontal plane at a distance of 25 cm from the",
                " target center: one at 125 deg, for absolute cross-",
                " section estimation of various reaction channels,",
                " and the other at 90 deg, for identification of",
                " unshifted gamma lines."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two charged-particle detector",
                " telescopes (DE = 20-30 um, E = 1000 um) were placed",
                " at angles 65 deg and 160 deg respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A monitor detector (=500 um) was placed at 30 deg.",
                "The solid angles of the telescopes and monitor detector",
                " were deduced accurately by measuring elastic",
                " (Rutherford) scattering from a 209Bi target of known",
                " thickness (~300 ug/cm2) at Ebeam = 26 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "GSPEC",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Online gamma-ray measurement",
                " technique.",
                "The coincidence between the 125 deg clover detector",
                " and the particle telescopes (TAC1,TAC2) was recorded",
                " in the ADC.",
                "The FERA-based data acquisition system was used for",
                " high count rates."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For Xe-126,128,130 production, gamma-ray production",
                " cross sections were measured for various transitions",
                " in the ground-state rotational band, and then",
                " extrapolation to J=0 to get the corresponding ER",
                " cross sections.",
                "For Xe-129, cross sections were obtained using the",
                " measured intensities of the 11/2- state at 587 keV",
                " and normalizing them with the results of the channel",
                " from the statistical model PACE.",
                "Fusion cross section was derived from the sum of 3n,",
                " 4n, 5n, a+2n cross sections normalized by the ratio",
                " of the sum to the fusion cross section obtained by",
                " the statistical model PACE."
              ]
            }
          ],
